hell yes to all of these points.

though the thing where you buy and unit (with the full board), put it down in the place of something else and try to sell this "old" unit will get the "new" one sold instead just sucks.
{{sticker:sg-soraka}}

Actually as someone that mains marksmen on my og account, I've found more success recently on my other account (this one) playing Ziggs, Brand, Swain etc in the adc position as an apc. Marksmen are so weak early and have 0 wave clear or CC tools that any combination of duo mages bot (Swain/Lux is pretty sick, Ziggs/Veigar, Any mage/Fiddlesticks) can pretty much destroy marksmen centric bot lanes by hard shoving and keeping pressure, because of said cc tools no jungler is going to dare go down there and try to risk getting locked down and blown up, but if you play a marksman if any other champion in the game sneezes on you, you'll fucking die. In solo q no one builds defense, most of the time the jungle and top are ad so you don't even really have to worry about having too much magic damage because magic damage is so overpowered. Let's not forget that last year Riot hard nerfed the shit out of marksmen decreasing their base defense and damage and scaling across the board. People are just so used to having a marksmen on the team, but they don't realize that marksmen are now just glorified dps tank killers, but god forbid you shoot at a tank with your BorK cause the team will get mad at you for not diving their back line or running past the tank (like he'll let you do that lmao). Mages have all the tools needed to dominate and control lane, there's a reason only like 3 marksmen can be viable in other positions but nearly every other class of champion can fill multiple lanes/roles on a team with nearly all the champions in that role because of the tools in their kits.

Let's also think about the people balancing and play testing; These are calm, cool, and collected people with a uniform intelligence and understanding of how to actually play the game, not you're average toxic-flame spitting-rage quitting solo q player that thinks they are the next faker if they weren't stuck in bronze. So, because you have smarter people balancing the game than actually playing it, it can make the game probably seem more unbalanced than it actually is. There's a reason the smarter players only play whatever's busted at the time, because the game isn't balanced and they know they can take advantage of that against players who just really love playing Teemo support, but outside of pro play, players are just not smart, don't keep track of cooldowns or anything. How many times have you seen a blitz miss a hook, and your team still runs away from him like he can still do something? Counter picks don't exist in solo q so that aspect of balance just gets tossed out the window in champ select, I don't know how many times I've seen someone have the opportunity to counter pick then pick something that's shit, and say, "He counters me I need lots of ganks." Or when my support picks pyke into a lux or morg or nami support and just hang out behind me and the minion wave cause he can't do shit into them. But marksmen are just there. Everything counters them. They don't really counter anything except themselves. I really feel that sometimes I'm fucking my team by picking a marksman in certain situations, but kind of feel forced to because of the history of the role and the fact that they are my FAVORITE class.

But yeah that's my little rant >_&lt;;;;;;;

